{"word":"ἀποσκοπέω","slug":"ἀποσκοπέω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἀποσκοπέω</b></el> <p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><i>to look away from</i> other objects at one, <i>to look steadily</i>, <el>πρός τινα</el> or <el>τι</el> <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b>; <el>εἴς τι</el> <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:accusative'>acc.</a> <i>to look to, regard</i>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>; so in <a href='S:Medium, Middle'>Mid.</a>, <b><a href='S:Plutarch'>Plut.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}